19/05/2004
NICE, France -- The third joint EU-NATO Crisis Management Exercise 2004 started Tuesday (18 May) in Nice. Participating in the exercise were non-EU NATO members, including Bulgaria, Iceland, Norway, Romania and Turkey. The exercise will continue until 27 May and is being carried out within the framework of the European Security and Defence Policy.
In other news, Bulgaria and Romania are holding a two-day international naval exercise in the Black Sea. The drill aims at boosting interoperability in anti-submarine battles. (Rompres, BTA - 18/05/04)
